<html>
<title>Contents Page For Tour of the French and Swiss Alps 2005</title><body>
<p>
This is the tour report for a 1964km Tour of the French and Swiss Alps
that <a href="http://piaw.blogspot.com">I</a> did in 2005, with Mike Samuel and Steve Purcell. At the end of
the trip, I had registered 36245m of climbing, with 4 flat tires in
all (me 3, Mike 1), one broken spoke, one torn up front tire from
off-pavement riding and a couple of wheel truings,
<p>
The original proposal (sent to an internal Google mailing list) can be
found <a
href="http://piaw.blogspot.com/2005/07/initial-tour-of-alps-proposal.html">here</a>.
<p>
When interested cyclists responded, I provided them with a <a
href="http://www.mikesamuel.com/alps2005/piaws_touring_tips.html">packet
of information</a> to help them prepare.
<p>
Mike also wrote up a separate <a
href="http://www.mikesamuel.com/alps2005/">Tour Report</a>. In
addition, a <a href="http://www.mikesamuel.com/alps2005/photos">photo
only page</a> is available.
<p>
